description:
Contract violation: postcondition

**Issue:** The function returns void but silently fails (just logs and returns) when state is LORA_UNINIT. Callers have no way to detect the failure.

**Code:**
```c
void lichen_lora_l2_set_rx_callback(lichen_lora_rx_cb_t cb, void *user_data)
{
    if (lora_get_state() == LORA_UNINIT) {
        LOG_WRN("Cannot set RX callback: LoRa L2 not initialized");
        return;  // Silent failure
    }
    ...
}
```

**Impact:** If a caller registers a callback before init(), they will never be notified the callback was not registered. RX packets silently won't invoke the callback.

**Fix:** Change return type to int, return -EINVAL when uninitialized, or document that callers must call init() first AND verify is_running() before trusting callback registration.
